column1: A CSR in my class locked themselves out of their application.  How will they complete the daily health assessment?
column2: The trainee will complete the Verbal Health Assessment at Security posted at the Employee Entrance and the Trainer will report the issue to their Training Manager to report the issue to the proper Point of Contact at the Local Site and the Site's Senior Manager.
column3: trainer.train(["A CSR in my class locked themselves out of their application.  How will they complete the daily health assessment? ","The trainee will complete the Verbal Health Assessment at Security posted at the Employee Entrance and the Trainer will report the issue to their Training Manager to report the issue to the proper Point of Contact at the Local Site and the Site's Senior Manager.",])

column1: Am I required to take calls while I train a class?
column2: Depending on business need Trainers may be called to the phones for Contigency. There is also a quarterly requirement of call taking for Trainers to meet.  Trainers may be granted a waiver while training class. See [Instructor Responsibilities SOP TD 1.21.01] located (https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/Resources/SOP/Training%20Delivery/Forms/AllItems.aspx?viewpath=%2Fsites%2FCCO%2FResources%2FSOP%2FTraining%20Delivery%2FForms%2FAllItems%2Easpx&id=%2Fsites%2FCCO%2FResources%2FSOP%2FTraining%20Delivery%2FTD%201%2E21%2E01%5FInstructor%5FResponsibilities%5Fv3%2E2%2Epdf&parent=%2Fsites%2FCCO%2FResources%2FSOP%2FTraining%20Delivery) see [Process TD 1.21.01.6: CCO Support] Step 6

column1: Are there a list of steps to load the courses in CCO Learning to my training class?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: Assigning the proper courses in CCO Learning?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the folder for the Line of Business you are training to assign  and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: How do I assign courses through CCO Learning to my class?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: How do I get curriculum assigned to my class?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: How do I push curriculum in CCO Learning?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. column1: How push courses and what are the proper courses to push on CCO once there is access?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the folder for the Line of Business you are training to assign  and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.
column3: trainer.train(["How push courses and what are the proper courses to push on CCO once there is access?","Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees. Click Finish.",])

column1: How to address questions about payroll and incentives?

column1: How to assign on CCO Learning for your assigned new hires?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: How to handle the clear2work app if a trainee gets locked out of the app?
column2: The trainee will complete the Verbal Health Assessment at Security posted at the Employee Entrance and the Trainer will report the issue to their Training Manager to report the issue to the proper Point of Contact at the Local Site and the Site's Senior Manager.

column1: I need CandidateRecruiting and Operations Portal data for my class. Where do I find that?
column2: Access [CROP Home](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Home.aspx) locate your Region. Locate [Administration](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Administration.aspx) on the left hand side of the home page and then find [DTR Export](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/Lists/theField/TrainingDTRExport.aspx) under [Export Views]. Export to Excel and then copy and paste to your DTR.
column3: trainer.train(["I need CandidateRecruiting and Operations Portal data for my class. Where do I find that?","Access [CROP Home](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Home.aspx) locate your Region. Export to Excel and then copy and paste to your DTR.",])

column1: I need to push the materials out to my class.  How do I do that?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: Is there a way to correct a ticket after it was submitted?
column2: 1. Go to [IT Service Help Desk Cherwell] (https://itservicedesk.maximus.com/CherwellPortal/IT?_=6c6a1b39)  2. Log in using  your employee number and Outlook password 3. Click My Tickets.  4. Find the ticket submitted in error. 5. Close the ticket or add a comment explaining and correcting.

column1: What am I supposed to do when a CSR tells me they resign?
column2: Ask the trainee to send their resignation to you via email with their reason suchas they found another job. Ask the trainee to also complete and sign their time card, go with them to their locker to ensure is clear and ready to reassign and escort them to the Securty Post for them to turn in their badge to be deactivated.  Forward their resignation email to your Local Training Manager and let them know all the steps you were able to complete.

Forward their resignation email to your Local Training Manager and let them know all the steps you were able to complete.",])

column1: What are the steps to assign the materials to my class?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.
column3: trainer.train(["What are the steps to assign the materials to my class?","Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.",])

column1: What are we supposed to do on the final day of class?
column2: The Handbook for the final day of training is located (https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/Resources/BCC-U/TngDev/Materials/Forms/AllItems.aspx?RootFolder=%2Fsites%2FCCO%2FResources%2FBCC%2DU%2FTngDev%2FMaterials%2FMedicare%20Day%20Zero%20materials%20%2D%20Marketplace%20Days%201%2C%202%2C%2010%20materials&FolderCTID=0x01200048F7620D9C6D6449B86DA68CE1ED637C) and housed in the folder matching your class Line of Business. In addition to completing this agenda you will audit your DTR to ensure is complete, complete and send the Class Confirmation and send SWP eligible ETO. column1: What end of training class duties are due to be completed on the last day of a new hire class?
column2: The Handbook for the final day of training is located (https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/Resources/BCC-U/TngDev/Materials/Forms/AllItems.aspx?RootFolder=%2Fsites%2FCCO%2FResources%2FBCC%2DU%2FTngDev%2FMaterials%2FMedicare%20Day%20Zero%20materials%20%2D%20Marketplace%20Days%201%2C%202%2C%2010%20materials&FolderCTID=0x01200048F7620D9C6D6449B86DA68CE1ED637C) and housed in the folder matching your class Line of Business. In addition to completing this agenda you will audit your DTR to ensure is complete, complete and send the Class Confirmation and send SWP eligible ETO. Before the end of the last day of class, contact your Training Manager or the class POC to have your class complete their Level One survey.

column1: What is done with the information in our Weekly Status Report?
column2: To report local Training activities to the Training Leadership Team and they will report these activities to CMS including Instructor Observations, Phone Time and Certifications.

column1: What is expected as a class POC?
column2: A class Point of Contact (POC) is expected to do adminstrative duties for the class including updating the DTR daily, perform wellness checks as necessary, file training folders, deliver missed moduals, deliver attendance milestones and train occasional lessons if needed.

column1: What should I do when a trainee tells me that they want to resign from the company?
column2: Ask the trainee to send their resignation to you via email with their reason suchas they found another job. Ask the trainee to also complete and sign their time card, go with them to their locker to ensure is clear and ready to reassign and escort them to the Securty Post for them to turn in their badge to be deactivated.  Forward their resignation email to your Local Training Manager and let them know all the steps you were able to complete.
column3: trainer.train(["What should I do when a trainee tells me that they want to resign from the company?","Ask the trainee to send their resignation to you via email with their reason suchas they found another job. Ask the trainee to also complete and sign their time card, go with them to their locker to ensure is clear and ready to reassign and escort them to the Securty Post for them to turn in their badge to be deactivated.  Forward their resignation email to your Local Training Manager and let them know all the steps you were able to complete.",])

column1: What steps do I take to assign the materials for my class?
column2: Access CCO Learning-My Employees-Assign Learning to My Employees.  Then Select Management Action-Add Items and curricula.  Click Next. Select Users - Click box under Select Users- Names will populate under 'List of Selected Users' Add Checked. Click Next. Search for Items and curriculum using key words or Exact Phrases. Locate the materials to assign and add checked. Click Next. Review for accuracy. Click Finish.

column1: Where can I find the CROP data for my class?
column2: Access [CROP Home](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Home.aspx) locate your Region. Locate [Administration](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Administration.aspx) on the left hand side of the home page and then find [DTR Export](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/Lists/theField/TrainingDTRExport.aspx) under [Export Views]. Export to Excel and then copy and paste to your DTR.
column3: trainer.train(["Where can I find the CROP data for my class?","Access [CROP Home](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Home.aspx) locate your Region. Locate [Administration](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Administration.aspx) on the left hand side of the home page and then find [DTR Export](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/Lists/theField/TrainingDTRExport.aspx) under [Export Views]. Export to Excel and then copy and paste to your DTR.",])

column1: Where do I get the Candidate Recruiting and Operations Portal  information for my class?
column2: Access [CROP Home](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Home.aspx) locate your Region. Locate [Administration](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/SitePages/Administration.aspx) on the left hand side of the home page and then find [DTR Export](https://maximus365.sharepoint.com/sites/CCO/bi/CROP/Lists/theField/TrainingDTRExport.aspx) under [Export Views]. Export to Excel and then copy and paste to your DTR.
